<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5350&amp;p=48417#p48417"><![CDATA[
Definitely look into split-screen scrolling.  That's usually the thing to do.<br /><br />It is possible also to do some scrolling in software (and CHR-RAM).  On the menu screen for Garage Cart #1 I did that, the actual menu itself is surrounded by a tiled, scrolling (and mis-spelled!) Membler Industries logo.  But the logo was 8x2,  which is 256 bytes to modify, then copy during vblank.  I don't know if you could get a good result with a 13x2 logo because you'll run out of vblank time unless you pull out every possible trick.  I know that's probably not what you want, but it can be a pretty cool effect anyways.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Mon Jun 29, 2009 2:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
