<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5350&amp;p=48401#p48401"><![CDATA[
I see... Well, you'll have to figure something out. Depending on how complex the background is, there are a couple of tricks you could try.<br /><br />Some games use sprites with low priority (behind the background) to fake a background and use the actual background as foreground. That will work if your background is simple enough behind the text that it can be faked with only 8 sprites.<br /><br />You said it's a title. If it's a title screen, the easiest thing to do is just to redesign it so that no more than 8 sprites share the same scanlines. If it's not, it might be OK to break the text into multiple lines?<br /><br />If you'd like more suggestions, you could always post a picture of what you are trying to accomplish and explain what kind of animation you want so that people here could give you some ideas.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Jun 29, 2009 4:11 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
