<div class="quotetitle">dr00id88 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I assume in this case flickering will be rather VERY annoying.<br /></div><br />I guess. This is one of the biggest limitations of the NES. We're used to objects flickering in cases when there are many of them onscreen, but it's usually temporary because of them moving around, so it isn't so annoying. <br /><br />However, if those 17 sprites you talked about are part of the same object, or different objects that are supposed to be aligned for long periods of time, the flickering will be quite distracting. Might I ask why do you need so many sprites lined up?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Jun 29, 2009 3:09 am</p><hr />
